column_comment: The formal name used when the banking institution refers to the credit card. Often quite long and can include various marks. If present, the name of the issuing bank is stripped

The informal name typically used to refer to the card conversationally. This name is structured so that it can always be prepended with the issuing bank name, and can allways be appended with the word 'card'
The abbreviation for the card, if one is conventionally used (not typical)
Whether the card is a personal or business card
Whether the card is a credit card or charge card
Whether the card is a secured card
The annual fee associated with the card, if it has one
Whether the card is presently open for applications; is not open for applications but can be product changed into; or the card is discontinued
The payment processer used for the card
If applicable, the product tier assigned by the payment processer used for the card
The issuing bank for the card
The currency the card earns as rewards from use
The sanitized official URL for the credit card from the issuing bank. (This is the promotional page URL, not the application page)
The sanitized official URL for the credit card from the cobrand partner, if applicable
Reference Points' referral URL for the card, if applicable
The direct URL for the card's artwork, hosted on Reference Points' CDN
Transferrable, point or mile
Point or mile
The loyalty program from which transferred points originate
The loyalty program to which transferred points arrive
The fully reduced numerator of the conversion ratio
The fully reduced denominator of the conversion ratio
The quoted or observed speed in which transfers are processed, in hours. A transfer speed of 0 represents an instantaneous transfer speed
The minimum amount of origin currency to complete a transfer
The maximum amount of origin currency allowed to transfer at a time
The smallest increment of currency that a transfer amount can be adjusted by
The quantity of destination currency that is provided as an additional transfer bonus, when the transfer bonus unit is met
The quantity of origin currency that must be transferred to realize a transfer bonus
Whether or not the partnership is currently active
Whether the transfer is available to the public, restricted to a defined group, or targeted
The primary source describing the transfer partner relationship
The name of the payment processor
